'''''Dungeon of Death''''' is a [[fantasy]] [[role-playing video game]] developed by Instant Software.<ref name="manual">{{cite web|title=Dungeon of Death Manual|url=http://www.mocagh.org/firstera/dungeonofdeath.pdf}}</ref> The game was released on the 8K [[Commodore PET]].

==Plot==
''Dungeon of Death'' is a game in which the player searches a 12-level [[dungeon crawl|dungeon]] for the Holy Grail.<ref name="Dragon44"/>

==Reception==
The game was reviewed in ''[[Dragon (magazine)|The Dragon]]'' #44 by Mark Herro.  Herro described the game as "one of the many quasi-''[[Dungeons & Dragons|D&D]]'' programs on the market" at the time. He also stated that "''Dungeon of Death'' provides "a 'cheap and dirty' fix" for the solitary game player.<ref name="Dragon44">{{cite journal
